     when's the last time you were on a vox or naggy raid?  you're very condemning considering the criticism you offer is towards raids you no longer qualify for.  not all raid leaders are people looking for epic pieces and they're not all doing it just for the loot either.  considering the number of drops that occur at these raids, what are the chances of walking away with anything?  considering the number of people it takes to pull off a successful raid, the odds aren't very good.  the last vox raid had over 30 people rolling on one particular item.  one person walked away with it and it wasn't the raid leader.  he didn't roll for ANY loot.  he was there leading us because he enjoys doing it.  and he'll be there again this week.  will he walk away with any loot or even any exp?  probably not.  he'll be lucky if he walks away without losing exp but he'll still be right back there the next time.  these raids aren't about the loot for most of us. there may be the rare time when someone will leave upset because an epic item is defaulted but it happens and most of us understand that.  for the most part, the raids are well organized and we have the leaders to thank for that.  they're there working harder than most people realize, enduring endless tells and trying to keep things progressing as fast as possible when it would be so much easier for them to just be one of the masses gathered there ready to kill anything that wanders by.  and once it's all over, imagine getting tells from 30 people all at once saying 'i'm in on that item'.  our leaders should be commended for the jobs that they perform, not criticized.<br>
